reviews.text: The botanic gardens are beautiful! Very well kept. I enjoyed the greenhouses too, such a variety of lovely plants. I can tell a lot of care goes in to looking after them. I wish there were some animals in the tropical house. Nice for an afternoon stroll.

Really blissful ..you can have a good walk here.
of course when the weather is good.. 
You can see a wide variety of flowers.. well maintained.

The Ulster museum at one corner for the park is definitely worth a visit...& there is no entry fee.
Wonderful gardens, and amazing hot houses. Beautifully set out.  And with the Ulster Museum on the grounds. Amazing.  All lovers of plant life, and Creation in general will enjoy time spent here.

Had a great day walking around the craft fair. Seen many spectacular flowers, massive vegetables and lots of stalls selling home made produces. The fudge was fantastic.

Found the Belfast ukelele jam group playing in a marquee. Wow great music.

Pleasant in the early Spring. The flowerbeds are full of vibrant colour. The hothouses are rich with blooms and scents. The lawns have not yet shaken off their winter rough and are damp, but not for long. The renovated tropical ravine is superb and the museum is nearby if it rains or you need a snack. If it's sunny, go and look at the herbacious borders; sit and listen to the bees at work.

Our regular hotel when staying in Bangkok, it has rarely disappointed us through our 10+ stays.
Staff is polite and service minded, front desk is usually quick and rooms are nice and, compared to many European hotels, quite spacious.
Big thanks to Suparp and the rest of the guys that greet us when arriving and help with our luggage. Always polite, smiling and service minded.
Breakfast restaurant is good with a huge variety of food, although I prefer to go outside for the local Bangkok taste!

The location is wonderful, right in the city center. Service is good, the staffs are quite helpful. Nice and clean, although a bit small.

Restaurants available everywhere and close to multiple malls like Siam center, Siam Paragon, MBK. The shopping mega Platinum is also just one station away, or if you don't mind the walk, there's a free walkway that takes you nearby as well.

فندق جميل وعجيب من الخدمه الي السكن في الغراف. وحتي الموظفين محترمين وطيبين وحتي الفندق قريب من المول سيام بركون 
Nice hotel! Great, convenient location. The check in staff were really friendly and helpful. I arrived early but Pump managed to find a room with no fuss and no waiting. Thank you!!
Great staff and service.  Good breakfast with variety. Close to everything.  Would stay here again.  Has a pool and a small gym.  Add pa as well.

This hotel wasn't really that nice. The only upside was its location within walking distance of shopping malls, restaurants, street sellers and markets, massages and salons. Personally won't go back as I didn't feel that comfortable there. Made use of the spa for a for massage which was pretty good.

Lovely Place to be. Lot's of variety in Ice creams. Superb price range. The place is not very big but you can enjoy the ice creams here. I love this place. They have take away option also with them. They accept Food card, debit card and all other payment options*. Highly Recommended...

Excellent location, parking mainly on the main road and side roads. Friendly staff, very fast service, hassle free service. Corner house has chosen right place to serve right people. Ambiance is not so great. Rates are inline with Corner House standards. Keep good work guys !

This is a very good place to eat ice cream and chill with your friends and family. The staff is really good and serve really fast. The place is cleanly maintained and they also have a washroom. Also do Try the death by chocolate highly recommend.

Well as the name like wise, this corner house is located in the corner of the building but easily noticeable. Ample space for parking. So budge in and gorge on their irresistible ice creams and what not! Happy ice creams to you.

They should rename their fresh strawberries to reflect how fresh they actually are. Cut in the morning and sold as fresh strawberries. Not good enough for 160 Rs.

Sad to see one of the decent places around cutting corners.
